added.title: Fat Cats
added.description: Teen Titans Go takes a comedic look at the superheroes' lives. Viewers finally get the opportunity to watch what life is like for the super teens when their capes are left at home. The teens will deal with everyday issues of adolescence including laundry contests and quests to construct the perfect sandwich.

added.title: Jam
added.description: Harley Quinn, Poison Ivy, and Catwoman recruit Starfire and Raven for their roller deby team.

added.title: The Legend of the Library
added.description: When the library is thrown into disarray, an ancient ghost is awoken.

added.title: Thingameroo
added.description: When a lack of motivation threatens to sink the kids' chances in the Sportslete Athlaction Awards, they create the greatest mascot of all time to boost school spirit.

added.title: CodE.T.
added.description: When Cody gets sick, the kids want send a message back to his home planet in hopes that they can save him, but Courtney is not in favor of this plan.

added.title: Plan-De-Monium
added.description: Val has meticulously planned for the perfect day of activities with Isabella, but his rigid insistence on sticking to the itinerary make for a less than perfect experience.

added.title: #EnterNightSting
added.description: Karen is given a mission to prevent the apocalypse by DeathSting, a super-cool future version of herself.

added.title: #WorldsFinest
added.description: When PR whiz Max Lord tells Batgirl and Supergirl he can improve their image by doing publicity stunts, the two friends forget what being a hero is really about.

added.title: #WorkingStiff
added.description: After Babs hooks Karen up with a job at the Burrito Bucket the two heroes encounter a new villain, the scourge of the fast-food underworld, the Condiment King!

added.title: #DetentionClub
added.description: Five socially disparate teens, Hal, Pam, Kara, Zee and Garth, find they have more in common than they thought after spending a Saturday in detention.

added.title: #SmallVictories
added.description: A malfunctioning device shrinks Karen into the Microverse, leaving technophobic Diana as her only hope.

added.title: #CruzControl
added.description: Working toward her dream of making her school a better place, Jessica runs for class president. However, when her opponent, the corrupt Oswald Cobblepot, pulls ahead in the race using less-than-honest means, Jessica finds herself compromising the integrity of her honest campaign to beat him!

added.title: #WhySoBlue
added.description: Supergirl must rein in a reckless new hero, the Blue Beetle.

added.title: Eyesore a Sunset
added.description: Art is subjective and Apple and Onion agree to let that get between them.

added.title: The Five Rules of Finding
added.description: Tiggy and Gweeseek use Chief's Five Rules of Finding to discover their own method of finding and locating Boss' missing tie.

added.title: Cat Burglar
added.description: While Tiggy and Boss work hard to cover their tracks after they're caught up in a cat burglary, a new churro cart catches Gweeseek's eye.

added.title: Hachiman
added.description: While on a super important mission to get batteries for the TV remote Lion-O meets Hachiman, a cool Samurai warrior. Now Lion-O will do anything to prove he's just as cool as Hachiman, even if it means risking his own life!

added.title: Schnorp
added.description: The Thunderkittens plug a new video game cartridge into Snarf only to learn that it didn't load a game, it loaded a whole new personality into their pal! Meet Schnorp, a kind Swedish man who loves the beauty of nature and collecting berries! Schnorp is loads of fun, but we're gonna want Snarf back, right?

added.title: Berb-cules
added.description: The ThunderCats finally sit the Berbils down and tell them they really shouldn't be building things for the Mutants anymore, it's time for the Berbils to stand up for themselves. The Berbils take this advice way too far and build a giant, building-sized, Berbil named Berbcules. Berb-cules takes back everything the Berbils ever built for the Mutants and everything they ever built for the ThunderCats! Now Panthro has to figure out a way to a defeat the most powerful invention the best little builders have ever built!

added.title: Pumm-Ra
added.description: Mumm-Ra plans to disguise himself as a Thunderian and infiltrate Cats' Lair, but the Ancient Spirits of Evil are mad at him and won't give him any magic today. No matter, Mumm-Ra knows what a ThunderCat looks like so he slaps on some awful, unconvincing, cat make up and heads to Cats' Lair to introduce himself!

added.title: King of the Machines
added.description: Panthro gets insecure when he finds out Barbastella has a history of dating royalty, so he tries to impress her by becoming "King of the Machines" and giving all the appliances in the Cats' Lair artificial intelligence.

added.title: Vengeance Is Mine!
added.description: Aspheera arrives at the Monastery of Spinjitzu and confronts Wu, forcing one of the ninja to make a heroic sacrifice.

added.title: A Cold Goodbye
added.description: Having learned Zane is not dead, Master Wu prepares to go after him, but Lloyd and the other ninja take matters into their own hands and defy their Master.

added.title: The Never-Realm
added.description: The ninja arrive in the Never-Realm where they quickly find themselves overwhelmed. Luckily, they are taken in by a tribe of Ice Fishers who tell them Zane has been imprisoned by the evil Ice Emperor.

added.title: Fire Maker
added.description: The Ice Emperor learns of the ninja's arrival and sends his Blizzard Samurai warriors to destroy them and the villagers who sheltered them.

added.title: An Unlikely Ally
added.description: Lloyd runs afoul of the Ice Emperor's Blizzard Samurai but is rescued by a strange wolf with whom an unlikely friendship develops.

added.title: Stuck on You
added.description: Tired of Axel and the team taking him for granted, Masko tries to get kidnapped and ends up stuck to Dynamo, who's less than enthused with his rubbery new sidekick.

added.title: Opposites Attract
added.description: Claiming he's good at heart, Dynamo convinces Axel and the team to help him find a battery that can power his centrifuge and free him from Madtrap's control - but Bobbie Blobby isn't buying the baddie's story.

added.title: The Thing in the Wall
added.description: When Axel and the team accuse Galileo of stealing their possessions, the lizard must hunt down the true culprit - a mysterious creature behind the wall - to prove his innocence.

added.title: Madtrap
added.description: Madcap and Princess SugarSalt trap Axel and the team inside a Minergy-powered labyrinth that attacks them with their greatest fears, forcing them to work together and escape as a unit.

added.title: To Tame the Perilous Skies!
added.description: With Axel's drone-wing broken, the team must find another way to stop Madcap and his minions as they take to the skies in toy airplanes for an aerial assault on the city park.

added.title: Shun and Lightning/Premonition of a Storm
added.description: Shun and Lightning: Shun and Lightning are on the hunt for a rare Tumpee, when they run into McQ! With all the devices related crimes happening in Los Volmos, Shun decides to investigate to try to get to the bottom of McQ's nefarious dealings./Premonition of a Storm: After a run in with McQ, Shun and Lightning find themselves in a little bit trouble. They're trapped!  Tied up with no Bakugan to help them escape, and no one knows their whereabouts. It will take some big help to help them get out of this mess.

added.title: Superstar Dan/Awesome Brawlers on Vacation
added.description: Superstar Dan: The Awesome Brawler's head to Tokyo for the Bakugan Battle League - Tokyo Edition. While Wynton, Shun, Lia and Lightning see the sites, and enjoy the tastes of Japan, Dan, as the Los Volmos Champion, has official Bakugan Battle League duties and obligations that keep him busy./Awesome Brawlers on Vacation: Lia, Lightning, Shun and Wynton explore the sights of Toyko when a rogue Bakugan shows up and rampages. The Awesome Brawlers have to spring into action, rolling out their Bakugan to stop the rogue enemy before any real damage can be done.

added.title: Bakugan Battle League, Tokyo Edition/Battle Royal
added.description: Bakugan Battle League, Tokyo Edition: It's the start of the Bakugan Battle League - Toyko edition! The first round will be a Battle Royale style competition, where only half the competitors will make it through to the next round. Along with the Awesome brawlers the field of competitors is filled with familiar friends and foes./Battle Royal: The first round of the Bakugan Battle League - Tokyo edition continues. The Awesome Brawler's and their Bakugan battle their way through the challenge and face off against tough competitors.

added.title: The Second Stage Begins/Mechanoids Attack!
added.description: The Second Stage Begins: With half of the brawlers eliminated, the second stage of the Bakugan Battle league begins. This round will be a timed race to the finish, with all kinds of tricks and traps that will slow down even the best brawlers./Mechanoids Attack!: Mechanoids have crashed the second stage of the Bakugan Battle League, causing all kinds of havoc. The Awesome Brawlers will now have to race against the clock, battling competitors and mechanoids if they want to make it through this round.

added.title: The Other Fight
added.description: Eliminated from the Bakugan Battle League, Ajit is airlifted by drone to a massive cargo ship in the middle of Tokyo Bay. Now that he's on board the cargo ship, he must rescue Dan and Drago, and stop whoever is sabotaging the Battle League. Dan and Ajit investigate the mysterious cargo ship that the eliminated brawlers and Bakugan are being held on. Dan races to track down Drago, but along the way runs into a familiar face.

added.title: La Venganza es Mia
added.description: Aspheera llega al Monasterio de Spinjitzu y se enfrenta a Wu, obligando a uno de los ninjas a hacer un sacrificio heroico.

added.title: Una Fria Despedida
added.description: Habiendo aprendido que Zane no está muerto, el Maestro Wu se prepara para ir tras él, pero Lloyd y el otro ninja toman el asunto en sus propias manos y desafían a su Maestro.

added.title: El Reino del Jamas
added.description: Los ninja llegan al Never-Realm donde rápidamente se sienten abrumados. Afortunadamente, son recibidos por una tribu de pescadores de hielo que les dicen que Zane ha sido encarcelado por el malvado Emperador de hielo.

added.title: Un Aliado Peculiar
added.description: Lloyd se enfrenta a los Samurais Blizzard del Emperador de Hielo, pero es rescatado por un lobo extraño con quien desarrolla una amistad peculiar.

added.title: A Domar Los Cielos Peligrosos
added.description: Con el ala del avión no tripulado de Axel roto, el equipo debe encontrar otra forma de detener a Madcap y sus secuaces mientras se lanzan a los cielos en aviones de juguete para un asalto aéreo en el parque de la ciudad.

added.title: Los Opuestos se Atraen
added.description: Afirmando que es bueno de corazón, Dynamo convence a Axel y al equipo para que lo ayuden a encontrar una batería que pueda alimentar su centrífuga y liberarlo del control de Madtrap, pero Bobbie Blobby no está comprando la historia del malo.

added.title: La Trampa de Madcap
added.description: Madcap y Princess SugarSalt atrapan a Axel y al equipo dentro de un laberinto impulsado por Minergy que los ataca con sus mayores temores, obligándolos a trabajar juntos y escapar como una unidad.

added.title: La Cosa en la Pared
added.description: Cuando Axel y el equipo acusan a Galileo de robar sus posesiones, el lagarto debe cazar al verdadero culpable, una misteriosa criatura detrás del muro, para demostrar su inocencia.

added.title: Pegado a Ti
added.description: Cansado de que Axel y el equipo lo den por sentado, Masko intenta ser secuestrado y termina atrapado en Dynamo, que está menos que entusiasmado con su nuevo compañero de goma.

added.title: El Hacedor de Fuego
added.description: El Emperador de Hielo se entera de la llegada de los ninjas y envía a sus guerreros Samurais Blizzard a destruirlos, y a todos los aldeanos que los albergaron.
